  "text": "The socio-economic impact of IBS, based on direct medical costs, decreased work productivity and increased work absenteeism, is substantial [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . A recently published review reported that the direct medical costs associated with IBS range, depending upon the study, from 1,562$ to 7,547$ per patient per year [CITATION_3] .",
